When you click the buttons for the first time, `currentLeft` is blank because your elements don&#39;t have the `style` attribute at that point and the else part of `if(currentLeft)` gets executed which sets left as the same value for both divs.

Set the left value with inline html style instead of css for your code to work

    &lt;div class=&quot;image-wrapper&quot; id=&quot;foo&quot; style=&quot;left: 0&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;image-wrapper&quot; id=&quot;bar&quot; style=&quot;left:-500px&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

Alternatively, you can keep the style in the css but use `getComputedStyle` like

    let currentLeft = window.getComputedStyle(element, null).getPropertyValue(&#39;left&#39;);

