### You specified a relative path.&lt;br/&gt;
Software that loads your HTML tries to request image from path:
`http(s)://BASE_URL/../../../Images/logo.jpg`&lt;br/&gt;

If you&#39;d open it in browser hosted on `http://somesite.com/folder/folder/folder/ContactEmail.html` it would resolve your image url as: `http://somesite.com/Images/logo.jpg`.&lt;br/&gt;

If it was opened from local file `file://C:/folder/folder/folder/ContactEmail.html` it would resolve your URL to `file://C:/Images/logo.jpg`.

### You need to:

1) Specify absolute URL (image *should* be hosted somewhere!)&lt;br/&gt;
or&lt;br/&gt;
